All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Applicant
Represents an applicant for housing projects in the system.
BookingManager
Helper class responsible for handling the booking process of flats for applicants who have been approved.
ExcelReader
Utility class for reading Excel files and converting rows into domain-specific Java objects such as Project, Applicant, Manager, Officer, and Inquiry.
ExcelWriter
Utility class to write various types of project-related data to Excel (.xlsx) files.
FilterMyProjects
Utility class for filtering projects based on various criteria.
Inquiry
Represents an inquiry submitted by an applicant regarding a specific project.
InquiryResponseManager
The InquiryResponseManager class is responsible for managing and replying to inquiries submitted by applicants for projects that an officer is undertaking.
IProject
Interface defining the essential operations for managing project visibility.
LoginService
The LoginService class handles the login functionality for users in the system.
MainApplication
The MainApplication class serves as the entry point for the project management system.
Manager
Represents a Manager user who can create and manage housing projects.
Officer
Represents an Officer in the system, who is both an Applicant and capable of performing additional officer-level operations such as project registration, responding to inquiries, and flat booking.
OfficerProjectManager
Manages officer-related project functionalities including viewing undertaken projects, determining project eligibility, and retrieving applicants.
OfficerRegistrationManager
Manages the registration process of an Officer to a Project.
Project
The Project class represents a housing project with details about units, pricing, dates, and personnel.
ProjectEligibilityChecker
Helper class to check applicant eligibility for different flat types based on marital status and age.
UIHelper
Utility class providing methods for standardized UI display throughout the application.
User
Abstract base class for all user types in the system.
